# Copy to .env and set for production frontend builds.
# Public URL of the Express API (no trailing slash). Required when the app is served
# from S3/CloudFront so /api requests hit your backend instead of static HTML.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.example.com
#
# Deploy-time: `npm run deploy:frontend` writes dist/api-runtime-config.js from HR_PUBLIC_API_URL.
# Recommended: copy .env.deploy.example → .env.deploy (gitignored) and set HR_PUBLIC_API_URL there.
# `npm run deploy:all` requires that value (or export it in the shell) so the SPA never ships with
# same-origin /api/* on CloudFront only.
#
#   export HR_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-express-host.example.com:5001
# If unset when using deploy:frontend alone, users can set the API URL on the login screen (backendUrl).
#
# Without rebuilding: set window.API_RUNTIME_CONFIG.API_BASE_URL in public/api-runtime-config.js
# (that file is copied to dist root; upload it next to index.html).
# Or in production the login page prompts once and saves the URL in localStorage (backendUrl).
#
# If you use same-origin /api via CloudFront (no VITE_API_BASE_URL), see:
# docs/cloudfront-api-routing.md
#
# ─── Zoho (direct API — weekly reports & Inventory) ──────────────────────
# Deluge / custom function webhooks are not used. See docs/integrations-zoho.md
# and docs/zoho-inventory-api-coverage.md (gaps for period columns).
#
# ZOHO_CLIENT_ID=
# ZOHO_CLIENT_SECRET=
# ZOHO_REFRESH_TOKEN=
# ZOHO_ORGANIZATION_ID=              # or legacy: ZOHO_INVENTORY_ORGANIZATION_ID
# ZOHO_API_BASE_URL=https://www.zohoapis.com
#   # or legacy: ZOHO_INVENTORY_API_BASE
# # Optional: ZOHO_ACCOUNTS_BASE=https://accounts.zoho.com  (e.g. .eu for EU DC)
# # Optional: ZOHO_FAMILY_CUSTOMFIELD_ID=   (Zoho "Family" custom field on items)
# # Optional: ZOHO_API_TIMEOUT_MS=20000
#
# If CLIENT_ID, CLIENT_SECRET, REFRESH_TOKEN, and ORG id are missing, weekly
# reports return 503 with code ZOHO_NOT_CONFIGURED.
